VINEYARD OFFSHORE, LLC THREE-DAY ADVANCED NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.2(c)(2)(B) of the California Public Utilities Commissions (CPUC or Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, Vineyard Offshore, LLC (Vineyard Offshore) hereby gives advanced notice of two scheduled ex parte meetings. The first meeting is scheduled for August 19, 2024, at 12:30 p.m. The meeting will be with Karolina Maslanka, advisor to President Alice Busching Reynolds, and with Suzanne Thompson and Maria Sotero, advisors to Commissioner John Reynolds. The second meeting is scheduled for August 23, 2024, at 9:30 a.m. The meeting will be with Jason Symonds, advisor to Commissioner Karen Douglas. The purpose of each meeting is to discuss the Proposed Decision determining need for centralized procurement of long lead-time resources, and in particular, the provisions involving offshore wind development in California. Both meetings will take place via WebEx, and each is expected to last thirty minutes. Participants representing Vineyard Offshore at both meetings are expected to include Rick Umoff, Director of Government Affairs, West Coast for Vineyard Offshore; Carrie Hitt, Senior Director, Grid and Transmission Policy for Vineyard Offshore; Michael Hagerty, Principal, The Brattle Group; Maureen Gorsen, Partner at Sidley Austin LLP; and Kenneth Irvin, Partner at Sidley Austin LLP.

NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATIONOF INVENERGY, LLC. Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), Invenergy provides this notice of an ex parte meeting with Karin Sung, Chief of Staff and Legal Advisor to Commissioner Darcie Houck and Amanda Singh, Deputy Chief of Staff and Energy Advisor to Commissioner Darcie Houck. The meeting occurred on Tuesday, March 12, 2024, from 3pm - 3:30pm via WebEx. The following non-CPUC persons in attendance were Jessica Yarnall Loarie, Invenergy; Poonum Agrawal, Invenergy; Manal Yamout McDermid, Caliber Strategies; and Shayla Funk, Caliber Strategies. During the meeting, Invenergy discussed offshore wind developments in California and general market transformation policies. Additional discussion included the importance of offshore wind in Rulemaking 20-05-003, the Integrated Resource Plan (IRP) proceeding, the IRP's role in California's transmission planning, and future regulatory processes mentioned in the Decision Adopting 2023 Preferred System Plan And Related Matters, And Addressing Two Petitions For Modification. No written materials were provided for the meeting. Respectfully submitted on March 14, 2024, in San Francisco.

NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION -LATE FILED Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), the California Energy Storage Alliance (CESA) provides this notice of an ex parte meeting that occurred on Friday, February 9th, from 11:30 a.m. to 11:45 a.m. with Karolina Maslanka, Advisor to President Alice Reynolds and Maria Sotero, Advisor to Commissioner John Reynolds. The meeting occurred by WebEx. Rachel McMahon, Vice President, Policy for the California Energy Storage Alliance (CESA) was the sole CESA representative in the meeting. In the meeting, Rachel McMahon discussed CESAs position on two issues relevant to the pending proposed decision in R.20-05-003.  First, Ms. McMahon discussed the need for a separate proceeding track dedicated to installation of energy storage at existing natural gas plant sites.  Second, she clarified CESAs position on contracting deadlines for long duration energy storage (LDES).  No materials were provided or presented.

CALIFORNIA WIND ENERGY ASSOCIATION NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), the California Wind Energy Association (CalWEA) hereby gives notice of the following communication on February 8, 2024, from 3:00 p.m. to 3:35p.m. via WebEx audiovisual conference with CalWEA initiated by Nancy Rader, Executive Director, CalWEA, and Dariush Shirmohammadi, Technical Director, CalWEA and Karolina Maslanka, Advisor to President Alice Reynolds, and Maria Sotero, Advisor to Commissioner John Reynolds. CalWEA discussed the importance of carefully aligning the CPUCs resource portfolios with applicants in the CAISOs interconnection process to ensure that planned transmission upgrades that are intended for particular resources (in this case onshore and offshore wind) can actually be used by such resources, as discussed in CalWEAs opening and reply comments on the Preferred System Plan.  No written materials were provided.

NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION BY MICROSOFT CORPORATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the California Public Utilities Commission’s (Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, Microsoft Corporation (Microsoft) hereby provides notice of oral ex parte communication in the above captioned proceedings.  This filing provides a summary of the May 2, 2023, ex parte discussion with Kerry Fleisher, Chief Advisor to President Alice Reynolds; Nick Dahlberg, Energy Advisor to President Reynolds; Suzanne Cassaza, Chief of Staff to Commissioner John Reynolds; Jake McDermott, Advisor to John Reynolds; and Caitlin Pollack, Advisor to John Reynolds.  The meeting occurred from approximately 3:30 P.M. to 4:00 P.M. via WebEx. Jonathan Noble, Senior Director of U.S. Government Affairs, Microsoft Corporation, Jordan Weiszhaar, Program Manager- Data Center Energy, Microsoft Cloud Operations and Innovation, Meredith Alexander, Consultant to Microsoft, and Carrie Bentley, Consultant to Microsoft, attended from Microsoft.   A three-day advance notice was originally only filed and served in R21-10-002, the Resource Adequacy proceeding, as the original intent was only to cover matters already in the record of that proceeding.  However, during the meeting it became clear that matters relevant to R.20-05-003, the Integrated Resources Planning proceeding, would be discussed as well in a good faith effort to comply with the Rules of Practice and Procedure, Microsoft files this report of the discussion in both dockets.

EQUINOR WIND US LLC AND BP AMERICA INC.’S THREE-DAY ADVANCE NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION  Pursuant to California Public Utilities Code section 1701.3(h)(2) and California Public Utilities Commission Rules of Practice and Procedure, Equinor Wind US LLC (“Equinor”) and BP America, Inc. (“BP America”) hereby give advance notice that they have been granted the following ex parte meeting in the above-captioned proceeding: On October 18, 2022 at 10:30 a.m. PT, a meeting is scheduled with President Alice Reynolds and Anand Durvasula, legal and policy advisor to President Alice Reynolds. Kelly Boyd, Lead Business Development/Offshore Wind US, Equinor; Jens Olaf-Okland, Senior Vice President of Business Development, Equinor; Matthias Bausenwein, Senior Vice President Offshore Wind Energy, BP America; Kathryn Dingle, Head of U.S. Offshore Wind Business Development, BP America; Michelle Orrock, U.S. West Coast Government Affairs Manager, BP America; and, Teresa Cooke, Policy Director and lobbyist, Brownstein Hyatt Farber Schreck, LLP, will be in attendance. The meeting will take place in-person at the California Public Utilities Commission Sacramento office in Sacramento, and is expected to last 30 minutes.

Interested parties may file and serve comments on the proposed 3-year integrated resource planning scheduled detailed in Attachment A of this ruling by July 6, 2020. The deadline for reply comments on the OIR is extended to July 6, 2020. Interested parties may file and serve reply comments on the proposed 3-year scheduled in Attachment A of this ruling, as well as in response to any topics at the July 14, 2020 prehearing conference by July 24, 2020.
